{"title":"Thwarted markets in everything, antiquities remain underpriced","link":"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/895832636/0/marginalrevolution~Thwarted-markets-in-everything-antiquities-remain-underpriced.html","date":1714848689000,"content":"<blockquote>\r\n<p>An auction house has withdrawn 18 ancient Egyptian human skulls from sale after an MP said selling them would perpetuate the atrocities of colonialism.</p>\r\n<p>Bell Ribeiro-Addy, the chair of the all-party parliamentary group on Afrikan reparations, believes the sale of human remains for any purposes should be outlawed, adding that the trade was “a gross violation of human dignity”.</p>\r\n<p>The skulls of 10 men, five women, and three people of uncertain sex, were listed by <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.semleyauctioneers.com/\">Semley Auctioneers</a> in Dorset, with a guide price of £200-300 for each lot.</p>\r\n<p>They were originally collected by the Victorian British soldier and archaeologist Augustus Henry Lane Fox Pitt-Rivers, who founded the University of Oxford’s <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.prm.ox.ac.uk/\">Pitt Rivers Museum</a> in 1884.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p>Here is <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.theguardian.com/world/2024/may/01/egyptian-human-skulls-pitt-rivers-dorset-auction-house\" target=\"_blank\">the full Guardian story</a>, indirectly via <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://twitter.com/samirvarma\" target=\"_blank\">Samir Varma</a>.</p>\r\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/2024/05/thwarted-markets-in-everything-antiquities-remain-underpriced.html\">Thwarted markets in everything, antiquities remain underpriced</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalr